      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:90:2",
      "text": [
        " يَجِبُ لِلْمُؤْمِنِ عَلَى الْمُؤْمِنِ النَّصِيحَةُ لَهُ فِي الْمَشْهَدِ وَ الْمَغِيبِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Ibn Mahboub, from Muawiya Bin Wahab, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘It is an Obligation for the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momin</span> upon the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momin</span>, the advice during the presence and the absence’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. It is narrated from him (narrator of the Hadith above) from ibn Mahbub from Mu’awiyah ibn Wahab from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “It is of a believer’s obligations to provide good advice to another believer face to face or in his absence.” "
        ]
      }
